    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 163, Number 36 (Wednesday, March 1, 2017)]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. ESPAILLAT:H.R. 1278.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:clause 3 of section 8 of article I of the Constitution[Page H1464]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <title>Ghost Guns Are Guns Act</title>
    <createDate>2017-03-02T05:13:47Z</createDate>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Ghost Guns Are Guns Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to broaden the definition of &quot;firearm&quot; to include any combination of parts designed and intended to be used to convert a device into a firearm and from which a firearm may be readily assembled. </p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-07-24T20:02:50Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-03-01</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2017-03-01T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
